<li id="cite_note-31">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="IBM_PC#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The IBM PC serial port is not strictly RS-232, since it uses TTL signal levels, whereas RS-232 requires signals of +/- 3 to 15 volts; some signal levels that are valid for a TTL high state, and all signal levels that represent a TTL low state, fall within the forbidden range of -3 to +3 volts for standard RS-232. (However, it is not difficult to design and construct a level converter that will convert between IBM serial port and standard RS-232 signals.)</span>
</li>
