<li id="cite_note-34">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="IBM_PC#cite_ref-34">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Sometimes the tracks were also referred as cylinders, which is technically correct and analogous to hard drive cylinders. One floppy disk track equaled one cylinder, however with double-sided floppies, only the first side's cylinder numbers were identical to the track numbers; on the second side, the cylinders 1-40 corresponded to tracks 41-80 of the formatted floppy.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-35">
